Section 1:
1 L.D. 390
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 VETERANS AND LEGAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 176, L.D. 390, “An Act to Raise the
10 Contribution Cap for Unenrolled Candidates”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Establish a Primary Election Period for Unenrolled Candidates in Order
13 to Receive Campaign Contributions in Amounts Equal to Amounts Allowed for
14 Enrolled Candidates in the Same Period'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 21-A MRSA §1015, sub-§3-A is enacted to read:
18 3-A. Contributions to candidate seeking nomination by petition; primary election
19 period. For the purposes of contribution limits under subsections 1 and 2-B applicable to
20 a candidate seeking nomination by petition, "any election," when referring to a primary
21 election, includes the period beginning on the day after the most recent general election for
22 the office that candidate is seeking and ending on the day of the primary election for that
23 office.'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment provides that,
2288 for the purposes of contributions by individuals, committees, corporations or associations
2299 to a candidate seeking nomination by petition, "any election," when referring to a primary
3300 election, includes the period beginning on the day after the general election for the office
3311 that candidate is seeking and ending on the day of the primary election for that office.
3322 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3333 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0058(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
